gomodel:SYNGO_1482  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The authors use paired pulse depression in GABAergic neurons of the CA1 region as an indicator of presynaptic site of action. They showed that application of a 5HT1a agonist in slices relieves depression and causes facilitation, as measured by eIPSC recordings. The authors also investigated the effects of the agonist in isolated nerve-bouton preparations to further validate the presynaptic site of action.\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- Term selected by expert ('integral component of presynaptic membrane (GO:0099056)') matches the interpretation of experimental data by the authors:\n\n\"We conclude that 5-HT inhibits GABAergic mIPSCs by inactivating the AC-cAMP signal transduction pathway via a G-protein-coupled 5-HT1A receptor and this intracellular pathway directly acts on the GABA-releasing process independent of K+ and Ca2+ channels in the presynaptic nerve terminals.\"\n\n- Although BP data may provide misleading clues on the precise localization of the regulating protein I follow the opinion by the authors and expert in this matter on the presynaptic localization of the 5-HT1a protein in this system.. Experimental description: Wisar rats from 10-14 D old (Methods)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1482" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

